data.title: DN5 8 Postcode Sector: Your Complete Guide
data.meta_description: Discover the DN5 8 postcode sector! Unearth average house prices, explore local towns and villages, find top tourist attractions. Your comprehensive guide to DN5 8.
data.text:
The DN5 8 postcode sector is within the county of South Yorkshire.

Did you know? According to the 2021 Census, the DN5 8 postcode sector is home to a bustling 10,863 residents!

Given that each sector allows for 400 unique postcode combinations. Letters C, I, K, M, O and V are not allowed in the last two letters of a postcode. With 244 postcodes already in use, this leaves 156 units available.

The largest settlement in the DN5 8 postal code is DONCASTER followed by Cusworth, and Scawsby.

The DN5 8 Postcode shares a border with DN1 1 (DONCASTER), DN4 0 (DONCASTER, Balby), DN5 7 (Sprotbrough, Barnburgh, Scawthorpe) and DN5 9 (DONCASTER).

The sector is within the post town of DONCASTER.

DN5 8 is a postcode sector within the DN5 postcode district which is within the DN Doncaster postcode area.

The Royal Mail delivery office for the DN5 8 postal sector is the Doncaster Delivery Office.

The area of the DN5 8 postcode sector is 1.78 square miles which is 4.60 square kilometres or 1,136.73 square acres.

Waterways within the DN5 8 postcode sector include the River Don.
